glosses: To sit down by putting one's knees down; to kneel down.
To bow down, to bend the knee, to genuflect.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish دیز چوكمك (diz çökmek, “to kneel down”), from دیز (diz, “knee”) and چوكمك (çökmek, “to collapse, to kneel or crouch down”), equivalent to diz + çökmek. Cognates with Azerbaijani diz çökmək, Uzbek tiz choʻkmoq.
